@version: [2, current]
@description: Constructor.
@lot:
- void
- string $in
@example: |
  $url = new URL('http://127.0.0.1/directory/foo/bar?foo=bar&baz=qux#foo');

  echo $url; // Return the base URL
  echo $url->scheme; // Return the URL protocol without the `://` suffix
  echo $url->protocol; // Return the URL protocol with the `://` suffix
  echo $url->host; // Return the URL host name
  echo $url->port; // Return the URL port if any
  echo $url->directory; // Return the URL directory if CMS is installed in a sub-folder
  echo $url->path; // Return the URL path without the `i` property
  echo $url->i; // Return the pagination index if any
  echo $url->current; // Return the full URL of current page including the `i` and `query` property
  echo $url->query; // Return the URL query
  echo $url->hash; // Return the URL hash defined by `$_COOKIE['hash']`
@example-description: Inspect URL properties:
@example-note: Most of numeric path value at the end of URL path will be moved from `path` property to `i` property. So, if we have `http://127.0.0.1/foo/bar/baz/1` then we would get `foo/bar/baz` in the `path` property and `1` in the `i` property.
